p: For example, a total of about 400 compounds was detected by GC×GC analysis in 1-16-EW (estimated from the number of peak contours in 2D plots) and, after subtracting baseline peaks, corresponding to fiber blending or background interferences, 137 peaks/compounds were identified. These results were in agreement with Wong et al. [ 20], where the 2D rational separation pattern aids the identification of ca. 400 metabolites in Eucalyptus spp. leaf oils, 183 of which were identified or tentatively identified and represented percentages between 50.8–90.0% of the total ion count, comprising various chemical families.
